This product is a pure-MLX reimplementation of inference for Zyphra ZONOS2.

It includes/derives from the following Apache-2.0 works:

- ZONOS2 (Zyphra) — the 8B MoE autoregressive TTS model, DAC 44.1 kHz codec,
  and speaker encoder whose weights this project converts and quantizes. Model
  and weights © Zyphra, licensed under Apache-2.0.
  https://github.com/Zyphra/ZONOS2
  This port converts the `drbaph/ZONOS2-BF16` release specifically, whose
  speaker encoder is an ECAPA-TDNN (2048-d). Zyphra's current upstream HEAD
  wraps a different (Qwen3-style) speaker path; this port tracks the BF16
  release, not necessarily HEAD.

- Zonos2_TTS-ComfyUI (Saganaki22) — the clean plain-PyTorch reference used as
  the porting oracle (vendored read-only under
  scripts/zonos2_oracle/zonos2_ref/). Licensed under Apache-2.0.

This project's MLX engine code is original work by the author. The DAC codec
mirrors the HuggingFace `transformers` DacModel; the speaker encoder mirrors
the released ECAPA-TDNN checkpoint shipped with ZONOS2.
